  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Validation of Organic and Mineral Soil Amendments for Organic Coffee in Boaco and Las Segovias</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmers, Coffee Farmers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will increase the knowledge of 200 organic farmers on the use of mineral and organic soil amendments for improving fertility in coffee plantations. The project will complete the study initiated under Alianza para la Creaci&#xF3;n de Oportunidades de Desarrollo Rural a trav&#xE9;s de Relaciones Agroempresariales (ACORDAR) to explore the use of soil amendments for increasing fertility and nutrient availability in organic coffee plantations through a second year of experimentation, data collection, and analysis in 30 trial plots distributed around the country on organic coffee farms. 

 This second year will allow for the measurement of effects of these amendments on yields and harvest quality, as well as other effects not visible in the first year of application.  A side product of this is also the validation and dissemination of a simple technology for analyzing soil fertility through chromatography as a tool for better decision making by farmers about fertilization.  The results of this research as well as the technological innovations under study will be widely disseminated among farmers and the coffee community through training events, publications and presentations.</narrative>
  </description>
